    "subtype": "equipment",
    "text": "This staff is made of a dense wood and strikes the ground with an imposing boom. At the top of the staff is a perfectly round obsidian sphere that, when stared at for too long, makes viewers feel as though they're heavier than before. When wielding this staff, you gain a +1 item bonus to saves against forced movement.",
    "traits": [
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 159,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "uncommon"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "f31704572455b8d77a8bd97c0045fde6",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "links": [
          {
            "alt": "Recall Knowledge",
            "aonid": 26,
            "game-obj": "Actions",
            "name": "Recall Knowledge",
            "type": "link"
          }
        ],
        "name": "Uncommon",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 11",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 11",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 11,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Something of uncommon rarity requires special training or comes from a particular culture or part of the world. Some character choices give access to uncommon options, and the GM can choose to allow access for anyone. Less is known about uncommon creatures than common creatures. They typically can't be summoned. The DC of Recall Knowledge checks related to these creature is increased by 2.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 5,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "8ca8a0ac0e16b3c136f09ca48d8578bb",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Air",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 452",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 452",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 452,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Effects with the air trait either manipulate or conjure air. Those that manipulate air have no effect in a vacuum or an area without air. Creatures with this trait consist primarily of air or have a connection to magical air.   \n  \nPlanes with this trait consist mostly of open spaces and air of various levels of turbulence, though they also contain rare islands of floating stone and other elements and energies. Air planes usually have breathable atmospheres, though they might include clouds of acidic or toxic gas. Earth creatures often find themselves at a disadvantage within air planes, as there\u2019s little solid ground for them to gain their bearings, which tends to at least make them uncomfortable.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 103,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "15e2d048ce93e7b648064b09972535bc",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Magical",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 458",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 458",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 458,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Something with the magical trait is imbued with magical energies not tied to a specific tradition of magic. Some items or effects are closely tied to a particular tradition of magic. In these cases, the item has the arcane, divine, occult, or primal trait instead of the magical trait. Any of these traits indicate that the item is magical.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 151,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "f6cdd9b53ed4b4a360df284df4503b27",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Staff",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 218,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "GM Core pg. 278",
              "aonid": 218,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "GM Core pg. 278",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "GM Core",
            "page": 278,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "This magic item holds spells of a particular theme and allows a spellcaster to cast additional spells by preparing the staff.",
        "type": "trait"
      }
    ],
